1
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:13,847
[theme song playing]

2
00:01:24,001 --> 00:01:27,421
[crunching]

3
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:29,423
Wow, it's been a long time.

4
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:31,842
Thank you for always taking
such good care of my father.

5
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:35,637
Gees, Sayu, you're all grown up.

6
00:01:35,971 --> 00:01:36,972
This is Yagami.

7
00:01:37,139 --> 00:01:40,142
[caller] Look, about trading the director
in exchange for the notebook...

8
00:01:40,392 --> 00:01:41,977
-It's been canceled.
-[all] Huh?

9
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:44,980
The new deal is this:
The notebook for Sayu Yagami.

10
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:50,360
Come to L.A. by yourself in two days
and bring the notebook with you.

11
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:53,488
I'm pleased to meet you at last,
L Number Two.

12
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:55,324
[gasps]

13
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:57,784
I am at the center of the SPK.

14
00:01:58,869 --> 00:02:01,580
You can address me as N.

15
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:04,333
N? Who is this guy?

16
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:06,084
Is he joking?

17
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:10,297
Like, this strange feeling, what is it?

18
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:13,717
IMPATIENCE

19
00:02:15,093 --> 00:02:16,303
[Light] N?

20
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:19,348
Why do I feel like I'm talking to L?

21
00:02:20,349 --> 00:02:22,434
[N] I told you that we wouldn't rely on L.

22
00:02:22,517 --> 00:02:24,186
But that's a bit of an understatement.

23
00:02:24,353 --> 00:02:28,190
The FBI and the CIA have explicitly asked
that I head up their investigation,

24
00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:29,232
not you.

25
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:30,525
Having said that,

26
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:33,487
we are outraged by the recent murder
of the director of the NPA

27
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,155
and feel something must be done.

28
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:36,948
After revealing the information,

29
00:02:37,032 --> 00:02:39,409
I believe there's a possibility
that solving this case

30
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:41,203
could lead to the arrest of Kira.

31
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:43,580
As such, I'm willing to lend you
my full support.

32
00:02:44,206 --> 00:02:45,874
[Light] "Lead to the arrest of Kira"?

33
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,292
Who is he anyway?

34
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:48,585
This confidence.

35
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:51,171
[N] Is there a problem, L?

36
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:52,214
[Light] No.

37
00:02:52,756 --> 00:02:55,050
It's just that following the death
of Takimura,

38
00:02:55,217 --> 00:02:57,469
Deputy Director Yagami's daughter
was kidnapped

39
00:02:57,552 --> 00:02:59,763
and we believe the same person
is behind it.

40
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:01,890
He's arranged for a trade in Los Angeles.

41
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:03,141
[N] A trade?

42
00:03:03,392 --> 00:03:05,519
The girl in exchange for the notebook,
I assume?

43
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:06,728
Yes.

44
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:08,730
Understood.

45
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,607
I'll have a team on standby in L.A.

46
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:13,110
But for now, they'll be working
on a need-to-know basis.

47
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:16,029
My cell can monitor the city
via satellite.

48
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:18,323
Or...

49
00:03:18,949 --> 00:03:22,327
On second thought, I'll let you have
full authority on this, L.

50
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:23,995
[N hangs up]

51
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:28,542
That's good.
It means we're taking the lead.

52
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:31,211
But what's all this about the Americans
not trusting L anymore?

53
00:03:31,294 --> 00:03:32,587
I don't like the sound of that.

54
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:38,260
Near, is it really safe to leave this case
in the hands of a fake L?

55
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:40,721
He hasn't had any success
in catching Kira so far.

56
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:43,724
I'm aware of that.
That's why it's a good idea.

57
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:46,727
It means there'll be an opportunity
to take advantage of him.

58
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:49,855
Of course, saving people’s lives
is important,

59
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:52,733
but as the SPK,
our primary goal is very clear.

60
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:56,361
We'll work to get the notebook
and capture Kira once and for all.

61
00:03:58,864 --> 00:04:00,532
-[Soichiro] Light…
-Hmm?

62
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:04,411
At this point, I don't care
if it costs me my life.

63
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,371
Please, just save Sayu.

64
00:04:06,955 --> 00:04:07,914
Promise me.

65
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:10,917
Stop talking like that, Dad!

66
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:14,463
You might have made your peace
with the idea of dying,

67
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:16,757
but have you ever thought
about how painful it would be

68
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,258
for everyone else you leave behind?

69
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:22,262
I'd never be able to forgive you
if you ended up dying in front of Sayu.

70
00:04:23,138 --> 00:04:25,640
Look, it's true that you might
lose contact with us.

71
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:28,935
But if that happens and you have to make
a split-second decision by yourself,

72
00:04:29,019 --> 00:04:30,896
then I want you to do whatever's necessary

73
00:04:31,021 --> 00:04:33,982
to make sure both you and Sayu
get out of this alive.

74
00:04:34,524 --> 00:04:35,692
Promise me, Dad.

75
00:04:36,902 --> 00:04:37,986
All right.

76
00:04:40,363 --> 00:04:41,865
[Misa] What? No way!

77
00:04:42,866 --> 00:04:45,535
You really want me
to go to Los Angeles with you?

78
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:48,830
Yeah, there's a chance I might need
to use your eyes this time,

79
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:50,874
so I want to have you close by.

80
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:54,669
Oh, Light! You're the best!

81
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:57,547
Oh my gosh,
I'd better start packing right away.

82
00:04:58,256 --> 00:04:59,925
[chuckling]

83
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:02,052
[Misa giggles]

84
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:09,226
Let's see, which one should I bring?

85
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:10,435
I can't decide.

86
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:13,730
Light, which do you like? Hmm?

87
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:17,651
Huh...

88
00:05:20,904 --> 00:05:25,992
[water pouring]

89
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:29,079
If things go badly,

90
00:05:29,788 --> 00:05:31,498
I may have to kill Sayu.

91
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,587
[bird chirping]

92
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:45,428
[Light] Dad, I'll fly to L.A. ahead of you
and make preparations for the handover.

93
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:47,389
Ide and the others
should arrive shortly after,

94
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:50,141
but to be safe, we should all arrive
on separate flights.

95
00:05:50,308 --> 00:05:53,395
Aizawa, I want you
to tail my father closely

96
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:56,606
and get on the same plane as him,
just in case something goes wrong.

97
00:05:56,815 --> 00:05:57,816
[Aizawa] Got it.

98
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:00,151
I'm gonna get a haircut
so they won't recognize me.

99
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:03,029
[planes flying overhead]

100
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,782
[Light] Okay everyone,
I'm counting on you.

101
00:06:26,928 --> 00:06:28,263
Mr. Yagami.

102
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,599
Who are you? One of the kidnappers?

103
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:35,228
You're going to board flight SE333.
I have your tickets with me.

104
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,397
It leaves from Gate 18.

105
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:39,274
Right, I understand.

106
00:06:39,858 --> 00:06:42,152
Someone has intercepted him at Narita!
Should I arrest him?

107
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:44,654
[Light] Calm down, Mr. Aizawa.
Don't make any sudden moves.

108
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,573
I can understand your concern,

109
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:48,783
but arresting him now
will accomplish nothing.

110
00:06:49,284 --> 00:06:51,578
Keep your distance
and don't lose sight of them.

111
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,371
[Aizawa] Oh, damn it...

112
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:56,583
They're boarding a different flight
than originally planned.

113
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,669
I'll tell them at the gate
that I'm a police officer and--

114
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:01,129
Get a hold of yourself!

115
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,798
You'll just blow your cover
and the operation would be ruined.

116
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:05,467
Can you find out
where the flight's headed?

117
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:07,469
Let's see... Huh?

118
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:09,471
This one's going to L.A. too.

119
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:12,474
Could they have somehow arranged
for another plane?

120
00:07:12,724 --> 00:07:14,059
Oh, this is bad.

121
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:17,979
[plane engines roaring]

122
00:07:24,152 --> 00:07:27,572
[air traffic control] Flight SE333?
Flight SE333, do you copy?

123
00:07:27,906 --> 00:07:30,492
Do you copy?
You have strayed from your flight path.

124
00:07:31,326 --> 00:07:34,996
[pilot] This is Flight SE333,
I read you loud and clear.

125
00:07:35,664 --> 00:07:37,540
I assure you, everything's okay.

126
00:07:37,999 --> 00:07:39,292
This is a detour.

127
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:41,002
[air traffic control] What is this?

128
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:43,797
You need to tell me
what's going on up there.

129
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,548
This is not a hijacking.

130
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:49,636
We're simply making a detour
and a quick stop to drop off a passenger.

131
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:51,388
[pilot] You can track us by radar.

132
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,598
However, if you attempt
to call the authorities

133
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:54,891
to interfere with our course,

134
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:59,187
I will not hesitate to crash the plane
and take all the passengers with me.

135
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:06,111
This is bad, Light… I mean, L.

136
00:08:06,236 --> 00:08:08,905
The Deputy Director's flight
has just changed direction.

137
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:11,282
A passenger's going to be
dropped off somewhere.

138
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:12,993
It can only be him.

139
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:15,286
Damn it! What the hell is going on?

140
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:19,332
I already checked today's flight crew
and passenger lists ahead of time.

141
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:20,875
No one on board was suspicious.

142
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:24,004
The pilot's a veteran
of over fifteen years.

143
00:08:24,087 --> 00:08:25,797
The co-pilot checks out clean too.

144
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:30,552
Then the kidnappers are powerful enough
to influence these people.

145
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:33,972
Uh, it looks like I have no choice.

146
00:08:34,222 --> 00:08:35,890
[dialing]

147
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:39,310
Director, this is L. Get me N.

148
00:08:39,811 --> 00:08:40,687
[Director] Right.

149
00:08:40,895 --> 00:08:43,982
[Light] N, I'm sure you're aware
of our current situation.

150
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,608
I need you to do me a favor.

151
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:48,445
Can you notify the airlines,
police, and military on your end

152
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:49,696
not to take any action yet?

153
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:53,241
What's he thinking?
I never realized he was this unreliable.

154
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:56,453
All right, L, agreed.

155
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:58,204
We'll locate the landing site

156
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:01,374
and keep surveillance over the area
using our satellite video feed.

157
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:05,170
If there's anything else we can do,
don't hesitate to let us know.

158
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:09,674
I have a message for you.

159
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,177
Put this in your ear.

160
00:09:18,308 --> 00:09:21,686
[Mello] Yagami, right now,
you're the only one who can hear my voice.

161
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:23,688
Listen very carefully.

162
00:09:24,773 --> 00:09:28,193
I'm the one who kidnapped your daughter,
but don't get the wrong idea.

163
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:31,529
I have no interest
in your daughter's life,

164
00:09:31,613 --> 00:09:32,614
one way or the other.

165
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:34,032
Or yours, for that matter.

166
00:09:34,741 --> 00:09:37,619
There's only one thing I want
and you know what that is.

167
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:39,579
The notebook.

168
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:43,958
Now, all you have to do
is follow my instructions.

169
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:45,835
If you do that, no one has to die.

170
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:47,629
As for the trade,

171
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:50,757
I prepared things so that both of us
can walk away satisfied.

172
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,218
Play along and there'll be no problems.

173
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:57,180
[Soichiro] I'm going to give the notebook
to some criminal

174
00:09:57,555 --> 00:09:59,933
in exchange for my daughter's life.

175
00:10:00,892 --> 00:10:04,896
When the time comes,
what's the right thing to do?

176
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:11,361
As a police officer, as a human being,
and as a parent...

177
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:35,426
[plane engines roaring]

178
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:38,346
[tires screeching]

179
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:51,860
[plane engines shutting down]

180
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:55,029
[machines beeping]

181
00:10:58,283 --> 00:11:00,660
L, we've been able to use
our satellite cameras

182
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,453
to pinpoint where the plane has landed.

183
00:11:02,704 --> 00:11:06,082
I'll send you a direct video feed
of what we're currently seeing here.

184
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:07,667
Dad!

185
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,252
[chuckling]

186
00:11:09,627 --> 00:11:10,962
So, what's gonna happen?

187
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:13,339
How will he make the exchange
in a place like that?

188
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:19,679
Hmm.

189
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:27,562
[mechanical whirring]

190
00:11:31,566 --> 00:11:33,359
[Mello] You see the entrance,
don't you, Yagami?

191
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:34,694
Go inside.

192
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:36,362
They're underground?

193
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:38,406
Well, well, isn't that interesting?

194
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:40,658
[mechanical whirring]

195
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:44,245
Damn it. An underground facility?

196
00:11:44,454 --> 00:11:47,165
The kidnapper must've predicted
that we'd be watching him by satellite.

197
00:11:47,457 --> 00:11:49,709
That means there's no way
to keep an eye on Dad.

198
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:53,087
[clears throat]

199
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:54,255
[gasps]

200
00:11:54,464 --> 00:11:57,425
[inaudible]

201
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:04,891
-[gun cocks]
-[Soichiro gasps]

202
00:12:05,183 --> 00:12:07,393
[gunshots]

203
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:16,027
[man] The glass is bulletproof,
understand?

204
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:20,031
This place used to belong
to a crime syndicate.

205
00:12:20,198 --> 00:12:22,283
They used to make trades just like this.

206
00:12:22,742 --> 00:12:24,827
We've made a few modifications as well.

207
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:27,288
Slide the notebook through here.

208
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:29,707
Once that's done, I'll release the lock.

209
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:32,418
You'll both step back
and spin the glass door.

210
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:35,797
The notebook will end up on my side,
and the girl on yours.

211
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:39,259
However, if you don't agree to this trade,

212
00:12:39,634 --> 00:12:41,803
I'll shoot your daughter
through this opening.

213
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,058
Hmm...

214
00:12:49,644 --> 00:12:51,437
[N] L, do you have a plan?

215
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:54,857
You can't seriously think
that handing the notebook over

216
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:57,944
to someone you don't know
is a good idea, can you?

217
00:12:58,653 --> 00:13:01,197
All right, Y462, proceed.

218
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:03,741
First, open the notebook

219
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:07,453
and insert it halfway into the slot
in the glass door on your left.

220
00:13:12,834 --> 00:13:16,379
Damn it! Damn it!
It's setback after setback.

221
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:19,424
And I've only just arrived in the US,
so I'm not in any position

222
00:13:19,507 --> 00:13:21,843
to start giving orders
to the American police.

223
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:23,136
[heavy breathing]

224
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:25,847
At this rate, the notebook's going be--

225
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:27,432
Light, is everything okay?

226
00:13:27,682 --> 00:13:29,892
Is something wrong? You look kinda--

227
00:13:30,018 --> 00:13:32,312
Misa, just shut up
and do what I told you, all right?

228
00:13:32,395 --> 00:13:33,730
[Misa gasps]

229
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:37,317
[Light] Look, I need you to keep killing
Japanese criminals so just do that.

230
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:40,695
This guy is obviously investigating Kira
and he won't give up.

231
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:44,115
If the killings are delayed,
we're in trouble. Don't you understand?

232
00:13:44,407 --> 00:13:46,951
Uh, okay. But who is this guy?

233
00:13:47,118 --> 00:13:48,745
[Light] Just get on with it, all right!

234
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:51,372
Taking out your anger on her, huh?

235
00:13:52,415 --> 00:13:53,583
Huh?

236
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:56,169
[ticking]

237
00:13:57,712 --> 00:14:00,006
[gasps] I can still make it.

238
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:03,885
But at this rate, is my only option...

239
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:05,595
to kill Sayu?

240
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:07,847
[man] Now then, I'll test the notebook.

241
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:10,224
[Soichiro] Test it?
You're gonna kill someone?

242
00:14:10,308 --> 00:14:11,768
No, I can't allow that.

243
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:16,105
We can't make the trade
without making sure it's the real thing.

244
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:18,483
Do you really want
to see your daughter die?

245
00:14:31,329 --> 00:14:32,455
[Light] I can't do it.

246
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:35,249
No one but the police
knows about this case.

247
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:38,211
If Sayu dies,
I can't blame her death on Kira.

248
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:41,214
-Argh!
-[all gasp]

249
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:43,007
[groans]

250
00:14:43,466 --> 00:14:45,051
What's wrong? You okay, Miller?

251
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:47,929
Look, that's what you get
when you steal from me

252
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:49,680
and sell goods behind my back.

253
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,557
He's a worthless idiot.

254
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,559
This is the first time he's been useful.

255
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:56,729
[man] Y462, the target is dead.

256
00:14:57,397 --> 00:14:58,606
[laughing]

257
00:14:58,773 --> 00:15:00,733
It seems the notebook
is genuine after all.

258
00:15:01,609 --> 00:15:04,779
Now, let it go. We'll make the exchange
for your daughter.

259
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:06,280
[sighs]

260
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:11,744
[gasps]

261
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:15,415
Dad, Sayu...

262
00:15:15,665 --> 00:15:17,417
Hey, they actually made it.

263
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:19,669
[Mason] The suspect is headed
for a helicopter.

264
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:22,964
Based on our intel, that's his only method
of transportation.

265
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:27,760
So this means we can be absolutely certain
that the notebook has been exchanged.

266
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:29,846
Hmm...

267
00:15:30,304 --> 00:15:31,347
[Light] Be careful.

268
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:33,933
We still don't know what they're planning
to do beyond this point.

269
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:37,937
N, I need you to maintain surveillance
of that helicopter until it lands.

270
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,648
Don't lose sight of it, no matter what.

271
00:15:41,691 --> 00:15:44,193
You seem to think
that's quite an easy task.

272
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,863
Nevertheless, we'll do what we can.

273
00:15:49,323 --> 00:15:51,742
[N] I'm sorry.
I'm afraid we've been tricked.

274
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:07,800
-[Light] A missile?
-Wow!

275
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:10,803
[N] You won't be able that with radar.

276
00:16:11,262 --> 00:16:12,847
Is the notebook on that thing?

277
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:13,890
[gasps]

278
00:16:15,892 --> 00:16:17,518
[rocket blasting]

279
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:22,773
[Rester] The missile's been launched!

280
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:26,569
The missile or the helicopter? Which one?

281
00:16:26,736 --> 00:16:29,030
[rotors whirring]

282
00:16:29,697 --> 00:16:31,699
Boss, I'm sure you were watching.

283
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:34,202
I did everything you asked me to,
just like we planned.

284
00:16:35,453 --> 00:16:37,371
Yeah, I saw that. Good job.

285
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:40,541
Then this is gonna wipe out
all those past screw-ups of mine, right?

286
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,628
Oh yeah, wiped out for sure.

287
00:16:44,337 --> 00:16:45,546
Do it!

288
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:50,343
[bleeping]

289
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:52,261
Near, the helicopter...

290
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:53,346
I thought so.

291
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:56,682
In that case, it means the notebook
is definitely on the missile.

292
00:16:57,225 --> 00:16:59,143
Damn! We can't track it.

293
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:01,395
We've lost the signal.
It could be anywhere now.

294
00:17:04,065 --> 00:17:06,400
[machines bleeping]

295
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:10,696
[gasps]

296
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,240
[grunts in frustration]

297
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:45,147
[splashing]

298
00:17:55,116 --> 00:17:57,285
It won't be difficult
to retrieve the missile

299
00:17:57,368 --> 00:17:59,203
once it lands in a deserted area.

300
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:02,582
He would have already laid out
the flight plan accordingly.

301
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:05,835
He should be getting his hands
on the notebook any moment now.

302
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:09,714
And when he does, I have a good idea
of what he'll do next.

303
00:18:22,393 --> 00:18:24,604
[dice rolling on the floor]

304
00:18:25,313 --> 00:18:29,442
[groaning in pain]

305
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,945
[clattering]

306
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:42,496
[yelping and choking]

307
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:52,882
[gunshot]

308
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,134
[clattering]

309
00:19:02,725 --> 00:19:04,352
[gasping]

310
00:19:15,363 --> 00:19:16,447
[N] L.

311
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:17,823
[sighs]

312
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:21,661
Yes?

313
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:22,870
He got us.

314
00:19:23,496 --> 00:19:25,456
-"Got" you?
-Yes.

315
00:19:26,123 --> 00:19:29,794
The majority of the SPK's members
have just been killed by the notebook.

316
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,088
[gasps]

317
00:19:33,422 --> 00:19:36,509
L, you were the one who handed over
the notebook without a fight.

318
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:38,886
You and your people were totally helpless.

319
00:19:39,637 --> 00:19:42,682
N, are you saying
if you were in command,

320
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:44,517
you wouldn't have handed it over?

321
00:19:45,226 --> 00:19:47,812
No, considering their preparations,

322
00:19:47,895 --> 00:19:50,106
it would have been impossible
to avoid this.

323
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:53,234
There's really no point in us quarreling.

324
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:57,988
[N] I propose we work together
and share the information we know so far.

325
00:19:58,239 --> 00:20:00,950
For starters, I should admit
that I have a very good idea

326
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,660
of who the culprit behind this might be.

327
00:20:02,827 --> 00:20:03,744
[gasps]

328
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:07,623
[N] I suspect the person who arranged
the kidnapping and the trade

329
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:10,000
is someone who goes by the name "Mello."

330
00:20:10,501 --> 00:20:12,294
[Light] Mello? Who is he?

331
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:15,673
[N] I don't have his photograph
and I don't know his real name.

332
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,300
All I know about him
is that four years ago,

333
00:20:18,384 --> 00:20:21,387
he was living at an orphanage
located in Winchester, England,

334
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:23,431
known as Wammy's House.

335
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:25,599
Wammy's House?

336
00:20:26,183 --> 00:20:28,060
That's the place Watari established.

337
00:20:28,853 --> 00:20:31,230
[N] I believe Mello
is playing a game with me.

338
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,650
He wants to see which of us
will be the first to take down Kira.

339
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:35,901
The final challenge.

340
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:49,707
Armo Justin…

341
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:53,085
It's Armonia Justin.

342
00:20:53,335 --> 00:20:56,505
Okay, um, I've got a little problem.

343
00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:59,550
I went to the king to report
that I lost my notebook,

344
00:20:59,675 --> 00:21:01,302
but after I described it to him,

345
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:03,429
the old man said
that Ryuk said it was his,

346
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:06,098
and that he had dropped it and took it.

347
00:21:06,348 --> 00:21:07,349
[laughing]

348
00:21:07,475 --> 00:21:09,643
What do you think I should do
to get it back?

349
00:21:09,894 --> 00:21:13,731
Guess you have no choice
but to find Ryuk and ask him yourself.

350
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:16,484
Yeah, that's what I thought.

351
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:21,071
So, I guess I have
to go to the human world.

352
00:21:21,572 --> 00:21:22,948
Yep, that's right.

353
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:24,366
Have fun.

354
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:26,494
Well, that sucks.

355
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:33,584
TO BE CONTINUED

356
00:21:38,506 --> 00:21:44,261
[theme music playing]
